{
  "data_contract": {
    "state_shape": {
      "gridSize": "number",
      "turn": "number",
      "status": "'PLAYING' | 'VICTORY' | 'DEFEAT' | 'FINISHED'",
      "allies": "Units may now include an optional 'range' integer field.",
      "enemies": [
        {
          "id": "number",
          "hp": "number",
          "atk": "number",
          "pos": [
            "number",
            "number"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "actionSequence": [
        {
          "unit": "number",
          "type": "'move' | 'attack'",
          "dir": "string (optional)"
        }
      ],
      "knockback": "Optional boolean on ally units; defaults to false.",
      "flank_bonus": "Optional integer on ally units; specifies the damage bonus added for each other living ally adjacent to the target.",
      "reflect_dmg": "Optional integer attribute on ally or enemy units that determines damage dealt back to an attacker.",
      "unmovable": "boolean (optional): If true, the unit's position cannot be changed by knockback effects.",
      "aura_shield": "Optional integer attribute on ally or enemy units that reduces damage taken by adjacent teammates."
    },
    "rules": [
      "REQ-001: Zero non-determinism (No Math.random).",
      "REQ-002: MOVE fails if target is out of [0, gridSize-1] or occupied by any living unit.",
      "REQ-003: ATTACK targets the living enemy with min ID at Manhattan distance 1.",
      "REQ-004: Enemy AI targets living ally with min Manhattan distance, tie-break by min ally ID.",
      "REQ-005: Enemy MOVE priority: X-axis reduction > Y-axis reduction > smaller resulting x > smaller resulting y.",
      "REQ-006: Turn counter increments after every ally action attempt, regardless of success.",
      "REQ-007: Enemy AI executes in ascending order of enemy IDs after every ally action.",
      "REQ-008: Immediate termination on VICTORY (all enemies dead) or DEFEAT (all allies dead).",
      "REQ-009: Final output is a JSON object containing sorted lists of living units.",
      "Output roster is full: allies and enemies arrays ALWAYS contain every unit from the initial state in ascending id, including units whose hp has dropped to 0 or below. Never remove a dead unit from the output.",
      "REQ-011: Ally units may have an optional 'range' attribute (integer). If present, the 'attack' action targets the living enemy with the min ID among those with Manhattan distance d such that 1 <= d <= range. If 'range' is absent or <= 0, the attack distance defaults to 1.",
      "REQ-012: If an ally unit has `knockback: true`, any successful 'attack' pushes the target unit 1 cell away in the opposite direction of the attacker (target_pos + (target_pos - attacker_pos)). The push occurs only if the destination is within grid bounds and not occupied by any living unit; otherwise, the target remains in place. Damage is applied regardless of whether the push succeeds.",
      "REQ-013: If an ally unit has a 'flank_bonus' attribute (integer), any successful 'attack' deals additional damage: total_damage = atk + (flank_bonus * count), where 'count' is the number of other living ally units at Manhattan distance 1 from the target unit at the moment of attack.",
      "REQ-014: If a unit has a 'reflect_dmg' attribute (integer), any successful 'attack' (where the target is living at the start of the attack) causes the attacker to immediately take damage equal to the target's 'reflect_dmg' value. This occurs after the initial attack damage is applied, regardless of whether the target survives the attack.",
      "REQ-015: If a unit has an `unmovable: true` attribute, any knockback effect (as defined in REQ-012) that would change its position is ignored; the unit remains in its current cell, while damage is still applied.",
      "REQ-016: If a unit has an 'aura_shield' attribute (integer), any other living unit of the same side at Manhattan distance 1 from that unit has all incoming damage reduced by the 'aura_shield' value. If multiple units provide such a shield to the target, their 'aura_shield' values are summed. Damage cannot be reduced below 0.",
      "REQ-017: If a unit has a 'phalanx_defense' attribute (integer), any successful 'attack' targeting that unit reduces the incoming damage by the 'phalanx_defense' value if there is at least one other living unit of the same side at Manhattan distance 1 from the target. This reduction is applied after 'aura_shield' reductions. Damage cannot be reduced below 0."
    ],
    "output_contract": {
      "fields": [
        "status",
        "turn",
        "allies",
        "enemies"
      ],
      "lines": [
        "status: <one of PLAYING|VICTORY|DEFEAT|FINISHED>",
        "turn: <integer>",
        "allies: <a JSON array of ALL ally units in ascending id, INCLUDING dead ones (hp may be <=0); each EXACTLY {\"id\":..., \"hp\":..., \"pos\":[x,y]} — never drop a unit when it dies, no atk>",
        "enemies: <a JSON array of ALL enemy units in ascending id, INCLUDING dead ones (hp may be <=0); each EXACTLY {\"id\":..., \"hp\":..., \"pos\":[x,y]} — never drop a unit when it dies, no atk>"
      ]
    },
